                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "deathNote": true,
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>When a graveknight is destroyed, their armor rebuilds their body over the course of [[/gmr 1d10]] days—or more quickly if the armor is worn by a living host. If the body is destroyed before then, the process restarts.</p>\n<p>A graveknight can only be permanently destroyed by obliterating their armor (such as with @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Disintegrate]), transporting it to the Forge of Creation, or throwing it into the heart of a volcano.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "ORC",
